But RASHEED, I think I
interrupted your ability

00:41:54.920 --> 00:41:57.190
to get answers to your
question from the table.

00:41:57.190 --> 00:41:59.053
RASHEED: A little bit.

00:41:59.053 --> 00:42:00.470
Yeah, so definitely
wanted to talk

00:42:00.470 --> 00:42:04.550
about some of these
Japanese paradigms

00:42:04.550 --> 00:42:07.580
kind of being a little bit
more pervasive in the way

00:42:07.580 --> 00:42:11.630
that they set up,
just like in the way

00:42:11.630 --> 00:42:15.620
they set up their whole
economic structure.

00:42:15.620 --> 00:42:18.410
And is there an opportunity
for different countries

00:42:18.410 --> 00:42:21.060
to sort of adopt different
paradigms in this way?

00:42:24.740 --> 00:42:25.740
STUDENT 3: To an extent.

00:42:25.740 --> 00:42:28.020
I think it almost goes
back to that discussion

00:42:28.020 --> 00:42:31.770
we had about our innovation
systems that makes them

00:42:31.770 --> 00:42:32.890
[INAUDIBLE].

00:42:32.890 --> 00:42:35.760
And I think while that
paradigm worked well

00:42:35.760 --> 00:42:38.500
for Asian countries, I think
there would definitely be still

00:42:38.500 --> 00:42:43.150
a lot of resistance in the
US if we tried to set up

00:42:43.150 --> 00:42:44.530
an identical paradigm here.

00:42:44.530 --> 00:42:47.850
People have these strong
beliefs about free trade

00:42:47.850 --> 00:42:49.530
and laissez-faire government.

00:42:49.530 --> 00:42:52.200
WILLIAM BONVILLIAN:
Right, although those

00:42:52.200 --> 00:42:57.420
are now right at the center of
a major political debate, really

00:42:57.420 --> 00:43:00.570
for the first time since--

00:43:00.570 --> 00:43:03.510
well, there was a debate over
these issues in the 1970s

00:43:03.510 --> 00:43:06.360
and '80s, a big
debate as Japan came

00:43:06.360 --> 00:43:10.770
to the forefront in two major
economic sectors in particular.

00:43:10.770 --> 00:43:12.600
And we're back to
that debate now.

00:43:12.600 --> 00:43:15.430
We're having it right now.

00:43:15.430 --> 00:43:18.310
And so all of this is actually
pretty interesting context

