in the US and why it's
dangerous when we don't have it.

00:57:36.410 --> 00:57:39.290
And he goes on to say, Mr.
Grove contrasted the startup

00:57:39.290 --> 00:57:40.910
phase of a business.

00:57:40.910 --> 00:57:43.070
What uses for new
technologies are identified

00:57:43.070 --> 00:57:44.120
with the scale-up phase?

00:57:44.120 --> 00:57:46.790
When technology goes from
prototype to mass production,

00:57:46.790 --> 00:57:47.660
both are important.

00:57:47.660 --> 00:57:50.095
But only scale-up is an
engine for job growth.

00:57:50.095 --> 00:57:51.470
And scale-up in
general no longer

00:57:51.470 --> 00:57:53.120
occurs in the United States.

00:57:53.120 --> 00:57:55.460
Without scaling, he wrote,
we don't just lose jobs.

00:57:55.460 --> 00:57:57.040
We lose our hold
on new technologies

00:57:57.040 --> 00:57:59.690
and ultimately damage
our capacity to innovate.

00:57:59.690 --> 00:58:01.250
He then goes on to
talk a little bit

00:58:01.250 --> 00:58:03.710
about laissez-faire
and open markets.

00:58:03.710 --> 00:58:06.530
But then he argues that
even though laissez-faire

00:58:06.530 --> 00:58:10.940
and those principles are good,
there is room for improvement.

00:58:10.940 --> 00:58:14.930
He talks about job centric
economies and politics,

00:58:14.930 --> 00:58:17.180
where in a job centric
system, job creation would

00:58:17.180 --> 00:58:18.897
be the nation's
number one objective,

00:58:18.897 --> 00:58:21.230
while the government's setting
priorities and arraigning

00:58:21.230 --> 00:58:23.278
the forces necessary
to achieve the goal.

00:58:23.278 --> 00:58:25.820
And within this operating, not
only in their immediate profit

00:58:25.820 --> 00:58:27.778
interest, but also in
the interest of employees

00:58:27.778 --> 00:58:29.360
and employees yet
to be hired, which

00:58:29.360 --> 00:58:31.430
is beneficial to the country.

00:58:31.430 --> 00:58:33.410
He ends with saying
something that we're

00:58:33.410 --> 00:58:38.005
seeing right now, which is
wealth inequality, that if we

00:58:38.005 --> 00:58:40.130
do have a place where we
just pretty much outsource

00:58:40.130 --> 00:58:41.180
everything, we're going
to have a country that

00:58:41.180 --> 00:58:44.150
has very high profitability,
but low prosperity, which

00:58:44.150 --> 00:58:46.692
is what we're seeing right now,
and especially very impactful

00:58:46.692 --> 00:58:47.850
in the last three years.

00:58:47.850 --> 00:58:50.552
Especially since after
2000-- well, in the 2000s,

00:58:50.552 --> 00:58:52.760
everyone started to outsource
all their manufacturing

00:58:52.760 --> 00:58:55.820
because it's cheaper
in China, Asia.

00:58:55.820 --> 00:59:00.340
But that's really hurt jobs
in the US in a statement.

